<HEADLINE> Canadian Foreign Minister Visits Fiji </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Foreign Minister
Lloyd Axworthy is in Fiji for a visit Monday, following the
conclusion of the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) forum
ministerial meeting in Auckland, New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
According to the Canadian Department of Foreign Affairs,
Axworthy will meet respectively with acting Prime minister of Fiji
Tupeni Baba and Noel Levi, Secretary-General of the South Pacific
Forum, which is the political grouping of states in the south
Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The meetings will be devoted to discussions on global warming,
conservation of ocean resources and the work of the Canada-South
Pacific Ocean Development Program.
</P>
<P>
"Fiji and the South Pacific islands are important partners for
Canada," in strong support for Canada's U.N. Security Council bid,
Axworthy said in a statement released by the Department of Foreign
Affairs.
</P>
<P>
Axworthy pledged his country would help raise concerns of small
south Pacific island states "at U.N. and other international
forums". 
</P>
</TEXT>
