<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks End Mixed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks ended
mixed Monday with the Dow Jones industrial average rising a bit
while most indexes falling.
</P>
<P>
The Dow closed up 1.90 at 11,030.33. The blue chip lost 50.97
points last Friday.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were lower. the Standard &AMP; Poor's 500
index fell 7.53 at 1,344.13 and the technology heavy Nasdaq
composite index fell 42.29 at 2,844.77.
</P>
<P>
Analyists said investors sold technology stocks to lock in
profits after the Nasdaq set a new closing record of 2,887.06 last
Friday. Yahoo, eBay and American Online dropped sharply.
</P>
<P>
The weak dollar also had a negative effect on the market. The
U.S. dollar dropped to 106.44 Japanese Yen today from 108.81 last
Friday, the lowest level since mid-May 1996.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE fell 2.09 at 620.81 and the American Stock Exchange
index fell 1.45 at 804.50. The Russell 2000 index of smaller
companies fell 1.54 at 439.65.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 13-to-9 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,753 down, 1,220 up and 556
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined to 652.22 million shares from 802.51
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
