<HEADLINE> Argentina, Zimbabwe Sign Accords </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 13 (Xinhua)-- Argentine President
Carlos Menem and his visiting Zimbabwe counterpart Robert Mugabe,
signed Monday here three accords including economic, scientific
and veterinary areas.
</P>
<P>
The treaty regarding economic and trade cooperation establishes
that both nations will escape dumping through agreed norms, and
will promote direct contacts between economic institutions in
order to favor the union of firms and investments in both
countries.
</P>
<P>
The accord of understanding in scientific, technical and
technological issues is geared to promote cooperation through the
development of joint programs on the matter.
</P>
<P>
The treaty regarding veterinary questions establishes that both
countries will strive to ease the trade of products and
subproducts of animal provenance to prevent the entry of illnesses
by infested animals in their respective territories.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents also held a meeting at the Government House,
during which they analyzed matters of bilateral and cooperative
interest.
</P>
<P>
President Mugabe began Monday an official visit to Argentina.
</P>
</TEXT>
