<HEADLINE> Two Killed in U.S. Elderly Care Home Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Two people were killed and
five others injured as a fire tore through a home for the elderly
Monday in Pennsylvania State, the United States, reports reaching
here said.
</P>
<P>
Some 35 people were evacuated from the elderly care home in
Brownsville of the state after the one-story brick structure
caught fire. Two nurse's aides were on duty at the time of the
fire.
</P>
<P>
A woman and a man were killed. Three women residents who
suffered smoke inhalation were in stable condition at Brownsville
Hospital. One woman was flown to Pittsburgh for treatment of
burns. Besides, a firefighter suffered minor injuries.
</P>
<P>
In all, there were 37 residents in the elderly care home, some
who use wheelchairs and others who need help walking, according to
the reports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
