<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UK Producers Prices Rise Slightly in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 13 (Xinhua) - Producers prices in Britain
rose 0.1 percent in August, leaving them 1.3 percent higher over
the past 12 months, according to the latest figures from the
Office of National Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The ONS also said input prices rose a seasonally-adjusted 0.1
percent, leaving annual growth at 3.7 percent, the highest in
nearly five years.
</P>
<P>
It is believed here that strong rises in crude oil prices have
put upward pressure on both input and output prices in recent
months.
</P>
<P>
The ONS said crude oil prices rose 5.1 percent in August alone
from July, to be a massive 70.9 percent higher than a year
earlier.
</P>
<P>
Core output prices, which exclude petroleum products and other
food, drink and tobacco, were unchanged on the month and still 0.6
percent lower than August 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
