<HEADLINE> European Main Stocks Lose Ground </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 13 (Xinhua) - London shares continued their
downward slide Monday as interest rate nerves continued to dog the
stock market.
</P>
<P>
UK's benchmark FTSE 100 closed down 22 points, 0.36 percent, at
6169.0, having pared earlier losses after falling as low as 6137
ahead of the Dow opening.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE Eurotop 300, a broad pan-European measure of the
region's largest stocks, also fell, closing off 0.75 percent at
1326.20.
</P>
<P>
The market avoided a return to its session lows, thanks largely
to a leap of more than 5 percent in telecom heavyweight Vodafone
AirTouch, the FTSE's second-largest stock, following confirmation
that it is in talks with Bell Atlantic to combine their US
cellular assets.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, the electronic Xetra Dax finished down 0.68
percent at 5446.91, dragged lower by a soft start on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
Banks lost ground, while chemical stocks got a lift from hopes
of higher export-related earnings amid a weak euro. Auto stocks
bounced, lifted by positive sentiment ahead of the Frankfurt car
show.
</P>
<P>
Paris' CAC 40 came under selling pressure after hitting a
record high of 4773.82 on Friday. The blue-chip index dipped 0.6
percent to end at 4716.78.  
</P>
</TEXT>
