<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pinochet in Hospital for Brain Scan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Former Chilean leader Augusto
Pinochet, who is currently under house arrest in London, was taken
to hospital on Monday for a brain scan.
</P>
<P>
The 83-year-old general was under close observation, his
spokesman told reporters. But no further details of Pinochet's
health condition was given.
</P>
<P>
"He has gone to hospital for a brain scan. He is having further
tests. He is suffering from various ailments and needs to be
closely observed," a Reuters report quoted the spokesman as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The brain scan is the latest in a series of hospital visits
made by Pinochet. He went to hospital for health check earlier
this month.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that he now suffers from a range of medical
problems including depression and heart difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Pinochet was arrested last October in a London hospital, where
he was recovering from a minor back surgery. He has since been
held under house arrest in a rented mansion near London.
</P>
<P>
A Spainish judge wants him be extradited to Spain to face
charges of human rights abuses in Chile during his 1973-1990 rule.
The judge said Pinochet is responsible to the deaths and
disapperances of 3,000 people.
</P>
<P>
Pinochet's supporters argueed recently that he is too old and
frail to face extradition proceedings.
</P>
<P>
The retired general's extradition hearing is scheduled to begin
in London on September 27, though Pinochet himself is not expected
to attend. 
</P>
</TEXT>
