<HEADLINE> World Cable Modem Shipments to Double This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Worldwide shipments of
two-way cable modems are expected to top 2.2 million by the end of
1999, doubling last year's shipments, according to a new data
product released Monday.
</P>
<P>
More than 1.1 million modems were shipped in the first half of
this year, compared to few than one million modems shipped in all
of 1998, said the report from U.S. market research firm the
Strategis Group.
</P>
<P>
Half of this year's modems will be shipped to customers in the
United States, with Canada, Japan and the Netherlands representing
significant markets.
</P>
<P>
As new markets develop, the research firm said, shipments are
expected to increase nearly fivefold over the next four years.
</P>
<P>
Motorola remained the global leader in cable modems in the
first months this year, delivering almost one-third of the world's
shipments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
