<HEADLINE> Singer Files For Bankruptcy Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. sewing machine
maker Singer said Monday it has filed for bankruptcy protection
because of its financial troubles.
</P>
<P>
Singer president and chief executive Stephen H. Goodman said
the firing Sunday in the U.S. Bankruptcy Court was caused by a
lack of liquidity following a recent decline in the global sewing
machine market and the bankruptcy filing a week ago by Germany
sewing manufacturer Pfaff AG. Singer acquired Pfaff last year.
</P>
<P>
Goodman attributed Singer's failure to the global financial
turmoil that has hit emerging markets over the past two years.
</P>
<P>
Singer, the world's largest consumer sewing manufacturer, is
doing business in 150 countries and regions. It was founded in the
1800s in the United States and moved its headquarters to Hong
Kong a decade ago.
</P>
<P>
Trading in Singer on the New York Stock Exchange was delayed
Monday morning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
