<HEADLINE> EU, Chile, Mercosur to Seek Free Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, September, 13 (Xinhua) --The European Union (EU) is to
begin separate negotiations with Chile and the Southern Common
Market (Mercosur) tending to separate free trade treaties on
September 15.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministers of the EU approved Monday in Brussels the
guidelines of negotiations with Chile and Mercosur, according to
reports reaching here from Brussels.
</P>
<P>
Negotiations for trade, political and cooperation accords of
the EU with Chile and Mercosur will be held in a parallel manner
as those of the European block with the World Trade Organization
(WTO).
</P>
<P>
EU authorities considered that European block's talks with
Chile and Mercosur will end in the year 2004 or 2005.
</P>
<P>
Chile is an associate member of Mercosur made up by Argentina,
Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
EU-Chile and EU-Mercosur negotiations came from the summit of
heads of State or government that was held recently in Rio de
Janeiro. 
</P>
