help with transport, logistics, communications and intelligence
rather than perform a classic infantry role of restoring order.
</P>
<P>
Rubin also said the United States was "considering" air drops
of food and other supplies for refugees there.
</P>
<P>
He said Indonesian President B.J. Habibie has indicated support
for humanitarian air drops "so the United States and other
countries are looking at the possibility of air drops of food and
other supplies to refugees in East Timor."
</P>
