<HEADLINE> Kenyan President Appoints New Chief Justice </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel arap
Moi Monday appointed Bernard Chunga to be the country's new chief
justice following the death of Zacchaeus Chesoni last week, the
Kenya Television Network reported.
</P>
<P>
Chunga, a former Director of Public Prosecutions, will be the
third black Kenyan to hold the position since the east African
country won independence from British colonial rule in 1963.
</P>
<P>
There had been speculations about who would succeed Chesoni and
 public opinion held that an indigenous Kenyan should be the
successor.
</P>
<P>
So far, among the 13 chief justices since independence, only
three were black Kenyans.
</P>
<P>
Chesoni, who was chief justice for less than two years, died of
heart disease after contracting bacterial meningitis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
