<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexico's Maquiladoras to Generate 12 Billion Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Mexico's maquiladora
industry is to generate 12 billion dollars during 1999, meaning an
increase of 2 billion dollars with regard to 1998.
</P>
<P>
The number of plants belonging to this field is at 3,259 as
esteemed in May and it is expected to rises to around 3,500 firms
in the coming years.
</P>
<P>
The "maquiladora" industry will have produced during 1999
around 150,000 jobs, with which the total number will be 1.12
million.
</P>
<P>
Maquiladora is a unique neologism designating in-bond factories
manned by locals and producing only for sale abroad. The capital,
and even installations are financed by foreigners. 
</P>
</TEXT>
