meetings. It adopted 309 resolutions -- 248 of them by consensus
-- and 130 decisions, he added.
</P>
<P>
"The variety and importance of the issues discussed at the 53rd
session and the serious and constructive spirit in which they were
considered show that, by virtue of its representativeness, its
universality and its ability to listen and look at from every
perspective, the United Nations remains the one central forum for
continuing the global dialogue on the fundamental problems
confronting the humankind," said the president.
</P>
<P>
The 54th GA session is scheduled to kick off Tuesday, during
which representatives from 183 countries are expected to take part
in the open debate, which begins on September 20. 
</P>
