<HEADLINE> Greek Equity Prices Soar to New Records </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Greece's equity prices
surpassed the 6,000 barrier for the first time in its history
Monday with the general index on the Athens Stock Exchange (ASE)
ending 5.09 percent higher at 6,032.85 points, its 49th record
since the beginning of this year.
</P>
<P>
The ASE general index now stands 120.38 percent up for the
year.
</P>
<P>
The FTSE/ASE 20 index also rose 5.02 percent to 3,180.21
points.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 480 billion drachmas (about 1.6 billion U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Advancers led decliners by 300 to nine.
</P>
<P>
The construction and banks sectors jumped 8.0 percent and 5.47
percent respectively. 
</P>
