<HEADLINE> Multinationals Now Contributing To Economic Growth In China (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 13 (Xinhua) -- It was a real eye-opener to
see the state-of-the-art mobile phones and automobiles on display
during the 3rd Chinese Investment Trade Fair recently in the city
of Xiamen in southeast China's coastal province of Fujian.
</P>
<P>
Big names like Ericsson, Nokia, Motorola, Ford, and Kodak were
showing their latest technology and products to demonstrate their
passion about, confidence in, and commitment to the Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
There were more than 60 multinationals, who are expected to
become a powerful force for investment in China, according to
Guido Magnoni, a representative of the Italian Institute for
Foreign Trade's Asia Desk.
</P>
<P>
Multinationals have been playing an important role in global
economic growth and international investment and account for one-
third of the world's output value, two-third of its trade, and 30
percent of the direct investment worldwide, and are a major source
of investment for countries worldwide.
</P>
<P>
Combining their investment and technology with China's immense
human resources and consumer market is an important way for China
to improve its competitiveness internationally, said Hu Angang, a
young Chinese economist.
</P>
<P>
More to the point, he said, it is the best way for China to
introduce overseas investment to help its big enterprises improve
and increase their presence overseas.
</P>
</TEXT>
