<HEADLINE> Xinhua Photo List for September 13 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Following is the photo list
for September 13 released by Xinhua:
</P>
<P>
1. Northeast China city of Harbin sees a spur of consumption of
household electric appliances.
</P>
<P>
2. Xi'an Ancient Culture and Travel Festival opens.
</P>
<P>
3. The renovation of the ancient buildings at the scenic spot of
the "Crescent Moon Spring" in northwest China city of Dunhuang is
completed and opens to the public.
</P>
<P>
4. Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji inspects the protection of forest
in southwest China's Sichuan Province.
</P>
<P>
5. The 7th informal leadership meeting of APEC opens in New
Zealand.
</P>
<P>
6. Diao Weiwei lifts 140 kg to equal the world record in the 63-
kg category at the fourth Chinese City Games.
</P>
<P>
7. Liu Haixia lifts 150 kg to equal the world record in the 69-
kg category at the fourth Chinese City Games.
</P>
<P>
8. China's NPC Chairman Li Peng meets with Japanese delegation.
</P>
<P>
9. China's NPC Chairman Li Peng meets with a French Senate
delegation.
</P>
<P>
10. Bobby Charlton, a senior consultant of Manchester United
Soccer Club, visits a Chinese youngsters soccer training school in
Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
