<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hurricane Floyd Speeds Toward U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Hurricane Floyd grew into
a Category 5 storm with 250 kph winds and headed toward the
Bahamas Monday, threatening the Florida coast of the United
States, U.S. forecasters said.
</P>
<P>
The Bahamas braced for Floyd, with the entire island chain
under hurricane warnings or watches. Officials in Nassau, the
Bahamian capital, said they anticipated a direct hit.
</P>
<P>
Floyd would pass Monday night or early Tuesday 190 kilometers
east of Nassau and could hit Florida State of the United States by
Wednesday between West Palm Beach and Cocoa Beach, forecasters
said.
</P>
<P>
A hurricane watch was issued for the Florida east coast from
South Flagler Beach to Hallandale.
</P>
<P>
Floyd was joined Sunday by Tropical Storm Gert, which formed
midway between Africa and Barbados. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
