<DOCNO> XIE19990914.0092 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Diplomacy Aims at Safeguarding National Interest, Promoting World Peace (7) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Opposing Hegemonism, Establishing Reasonable New International
Political and Economic Order
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of the 1990s when the bi-polar global
system collapsed and the Cold War ended, the international
situation has moved toward relaxation and a multi-polar system has
taken shape.
</P>
<P>
As the largest developing country in the world, China has been
an important force for maintaining world peace and stability and
has played an active role in promoting and developing that system.
</P>
<P>
From the Five Principles of Peaceful Coexistence of the '50s to
Mao Zedong's "three-world" theory in the '70s, from the south-to-
south cooperation of the '80s to the all-round diplomacy of the '
90s, China has shared the same basic interests of the Third World,
and those countries are now faced with the same tasks of
maintaining national independence and developing the economy.
</P>
<P>
The primary foreign policy of New China has been to consolidate
unity and cooperation with developing countries, which have grown
to be a major force in opposing imperialism, hegemonism, and power
politics, and in maintaining world peace.
</P>
<P>
The rise of the Third World is a matter of prime importance of
our times, and Third World countries have become a major force to
oppose imperialism, hegemonism and power politics, and to maintain
world peace. China places great importance on relations with these
developing countries and supports them in their economic growth
and in their efforts to promote south-to-south cooperation and to
establish a new international political and economic order.  (
more)
nnnn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990914.0093 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Diplomacy Aims at Safeguarding National Interest, Promoting World Peace (8) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the past several years, a new form of partnership among
large countries based on common interests, consultation on an
equal footing, seeking common ground while reserving differences,
and not targeting any third party has been established.
</P>
<P>
This new type of partnership has improved China's status on the
international stage and has played an indispensable role in
shaping trends in international democratization.
</P>
<P>
China and Russia decided to develop a strategic, cooperative
partnership oriented towards the 21st century in April 1996. Since
then, China decided to establish a long-term comprehensive
partnership with France, a constructive strategic partnership with
the United States, and a comprehensive partnership with Great
Britain.
</P>
<P>
Last year, China decided to establish a long-term stable
constructive partnership with oriented to the 21st century with
the European Union, and to develop a friendly and cooperative
partnership devoted to peace and development with Japan, when
President Jiang Zemin made a state visit to that country.
</P>
<P>
China has also established various partnerships with developing
countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990914.0094 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Diplomacy Aims at Safeguarding National Interest, Promoting World Peace (9) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The history of contemporary international relations has shown
that the time for a few large countries to control the destiny of
other countries has passed. At the turn of the century, anyone
intending to engage in power politics will end up getting punished.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang has pointed out that the world is by no means
at peace and that there have been new developments in hegemonism
and power politics.
</P>
<P>
He said it remains a difficult task getting peace-loving
governments and people in the world to maintain basic norms of
international relations, including the five principles of
coexistence -- mutual respect for sovereignty and territorial
integrity, mutual non-aggression, mutual non-interference in each
other's internal affairs, equality, mutual benefit and peaceful
coexistence -- and establishing a new international political and
economic order.
</P>
<P>
The new type of foreign diplomacy with Chinese characteristics
that was developed and refined by three generations of Chinese
leaders has effectively helped safeguard national security and
interests and has contributed to world peace and development.
</P>
</TEXT>
