<HEADLINE> Security Council Extends MINURSO Mandate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations
Security Council Monday decided to extend the mandate of the U.N.
Mission for the Referendum in Western Sahara (MINURSO) until
December 4, 1999.
</P>
<P>
The move came after the Security Council reviewed Monday
morning the latest report by U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan on
the developments in Western Sahara.
</P>
<P>
In its resolution, the Security Council said the mandate was
extended to help complete the identification of voters, implement
confidence-building measures and conclude all outstanding
agreements needed to implement the Settlement Plan.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council requested the U.N. chief to report every
45 days on significant developments in the implementation of the
Settlement Plan.
</P>
<P>
The current mandate of the MINURSO expires on September 14,
1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
