<HEADLINE> Second Day of Strike In Bangladesh Passes Off Peacefully </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The second day of a three-day
nation-wide hartal (strike) enforced by the Bangladesh Nationalist
Party (BNP) led-opposition alliance passed off almost peacefully
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to reports reaching here, life was almost normal
throughout the country including the capital. Most of the
government, semi-government and private offices remained open
during the hartal hours.
</P>
<P>
Different organizations of the ruling Bangladesh Awami League
staged anti-hartal processions during the day.
</P>
<P>
Police arrested 44 people in Dhaka during the hartal for their
alleged involvement in bomb throwing at police and pedestrians. At
least three policemen were injured when pro-hartal activists
hurled bombs and stones at them in different areas in the capital.
</P>
<P>
The opposition declared a three-day hartal across the country
from Monday to demand the resignation of the government and
immediate parliamentary elections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
