<HEADLINE> Thailand Consumer Price Index Higher in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's consumer price
index (CPI) in August rose to 128.0 compared with 127.5 in July,
according to a government house press release issued on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The CPI of food and beverages in August dropped 0.1 percent due
to the lower prices of pork, vegetable, egg, vegetable oil and
aqua-animals.
</P>
<P>
The CPI of other goods rose 0.7 percent because of the higher
prices of water, electricity, petrol and alcoholic beverages.
</P>
<P>
The CPI dropped 1.1 percent last month compared with a year
earlier. The average CPI in the first three months of this year
rose 0.5 percent compared with the same period last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
