<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand Remains Member of Marine Protection Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Thailand decided Tuesday to
continue its membership of a marine environment protection program
in order to get help in collecting oceanography data and studying
coastal resources.
</P>
<P>
A Government House press release said that the Thai cabinet
approved a proposal by the Ministry of Science, Technology and
Environment to continue its membership of the Action Plan for the
Protection and Development of the Marine Environment and Areas of
the East Asia Seas.
</P>
<P>
Thailand will then pay 20,900 U.S. dollars of annual membership
fee, the press release said.
</P>
<P>
By maintaining membership of the Action Plan, Thailand is
expected to get help in collecting oceanography data which is the
database for the plan on the release of waste water in sea and the
mathematical model for calculating the direction of oil leak in
the sea.
</P>
<P>
The Action Plan will also help East Asian countries to
cooperate to study oceanology and coastal resources.
</P>
<P>
From 1983 till now, Thailand has received supporting fund
totalling 316,485 dollars, compared to 67,900 dollars of its
donation to the program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
