<HEADLINE> Disney to Cease "Jerusalem, Israel's Capital" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Prince Waleed Ibn
Talal said on Tuesday he was assured by Chairman of Walt Disney
Co. Michael Eisner that the entertainment giant will not hold an
exhibition under the title of "Jerusalem, Israel' Capital."
</P>
<P>
Prince Talal, one of the major investors in Disney Land
Company in France, said he had contacted Eisner and briefed him
with the Arab stand, the Kuwait News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Prince Talal said Eisner promised not to interfere in the
Jerusalem issue before the final status talks ended.
</P>
<P>
Recent reports said Israel's government intended to finance an
exhibit at Disney world's Epcot Center in Orlando, Florida of the
United States, which will be held under the banner of "Jerusalem
is the Capital of Israel."
</P>
<P>
Arab states, which regard Jerusalem as the capital of a future
Palestinian state, have voiced strong objection to such a show.
</P>
<P>
The United Arab Emirates (UAE) last week threatened to boycott
all Disney products if the company hosts the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
Arab League Secretary-General Esmat Abdel-Meguid said in Cairo
on Monday the league had decided to send a team to inspect the
exhibition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
