<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Officials Urged to Study Theory on Socialist Market Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, September 14 (Xinhua) -- A senior leader of the ruling
Communist Party of China (CPC) has called on the country's leading
officials to study the theory about the socialist market economy
as well as new contradictions and problems in the course of
developing the socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
Hu Jintao, State Vice-President and member of the Standing
Committee of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee,
made the call during his inspection of northwest China's Gansu
Province from September 8-14.
</P>
<P>
While in Gansu, Hu inspected some key projects designed to help
poor areas and solve water shortage, and a number of large State-
owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the present rural economy, Hu said that the rural
leading officials must further emancipate their mind and take
active measures to readjust the rural economic structure, promote
farm production through science and education, and ensure the
steady growth of the rural economy and the farmers' income.
</P>
<P>
On the reform of the State-owned enterprises, the Chinese
leader stressed that the leadership at all levels must be improved
in promoting the reform of the State-owned businesses. All the
leading officials should be good at combining the general
guidelines of the central government with the actual situation of
the businesses in this regard.
</P>
<P>
He also visited Lanzhou University and the Lanzhou Branch of
the Chinese Academy of Sciences, urging the teachers, scientists
and technicians to make greater contributions to the economic and
social development of the western region.
</P>
<P>
Hu pointed out that the socialist market economy is new in the
history of mankind. China has experience to deal with inflation,
but has no experience to handle the issue of deflation, He said.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, leading officials at all levels must step up their
study on the theory of socialist market economy and the objective
laws of the economy, he urged.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese leader is confident of the future development of
the underdeveloped areas like Gansu.
</P>
<P>
While the international situation is going complicated and
profound changes and China's reform has entered a crucial period,
it is of great importance to maintain stability, Hu stressed.
</P>
</TEXT>
