<DOCNO> XIE19990914.0126 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Students Clash With Police in Indonesia's Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Students clashed with police
in front of Indonesian Christian University (UKI) in Jakarta,
capital of Indonesia Tuesday, and two vehicles were burned.
</P>
<P>
The clashes occurred when hundreds of students were marching
towards the Parliament building in protest against a Security Act
Law Plan which is being discussed by parliament.
</P>
<P>
The law would allow the country's president to declare a state
of danger at no clear limitation.
</P>
<P>
The law plan has been widely opposed because it would give the
president too much authority in taking security measures which
many say may lead to dictatorship.
</P>
<P>
The clashes started when police tried to blockade the students'
rally in front of UKI.
</P>
<P>
About 500 students managed to skip out of the campus, but they
were unable to continue the rally due to the tighter blockade set
up some 100 meters from the campus gate.
</P>
<P>
Tension mounted as students and police officers started
throwing stones at each other, although no major casualties were
reported. The students also threw Molotov cocktails at the police.
</P>
<P>
A military jeep and a police jeep trapped during the clashes
were burned by angry Students and local residents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
