<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Highlights of Today's Diplomatic News (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Following are the highlights
of the diplomatic news released by Xinhua today.
</P>
<P>
NPC Chairman Meets Foreign Guests
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee of China's National
People's Congress, met here today with A.M. Gleeson, chief justice
of Australian High Court.
</P>
<P>
Li spoke highly of Sino-Australian relations, saying both
countries are in the Asia-Pacific region, and thus enjoy a broad
cooperative sphere. He said the Australian High Court and China's
Supreme People's Court (SPC) have maintained sound cooperative
relations, expressing the hope that Gleeson's current visit would
further promote cooperation in this regard.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting today with Japan's Nippon Electric Co., Ltd. (NEC)
chief advisor Tadahiro Sekimoto, Li Peng expressed hope that NEC
would expand cooperation with the Chinese, saying that the
introduction of advanced technology will help.
</P>
<P>
He said he deeply appreciates Sekimoto's contribution to
bilateral ties and telecommunications cooperation between the two
countries since the 1970s, and hoped he would continue his efforts
in this regard.
</P>
<P>
To mark his outstanding contribution, the Chinese People's
Association for Friendship with Foreign Countries (CPAFFC) has
decided to grant Sekimoto the honorary title of "people's
friendship envoy."
</P>
<P>
Li Peng also met here today with an Albanian People's Assembly
(APA) delegation led by Sabri Godo, chairman of the assembly's
Commission of Foreign Affairs.
</P>
<P>
Li said China and Albania enjoy traditional friendship and
growth of bilateral ties was "generally smooth".
</P>
<P>
China respects the development path chosen by Albania, he said,
adding that the increased contacts between the NPC and APA
deepened bilateral ties. He hoped the guests could better
understand China, which would promote better understanding between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
NPC Vice-Chairman Meets Canadian Guests
</P>
<P>
Zou Jiahua, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress (NPC), met here today with William
Graham, chairman of the Standing Committee of foreign affairs and
international trade of the House of Commons of the Federal
Parliament of Canada.
</P>
