<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier On Financial Management </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Vice-premier Wen Jiabao told
a meeting here today that financiers need to improve management
and develop more services for the country's modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Wen said that they should first establish an internal mechanism
that avoids risks and stops corruption and that scientific
supervisory methods badly need to be adopted and internal systems
of control and self-restraint set up.
</P>
<P>
In addition, there needs to be a greater effort at improving
the quality of people working in finances.
</P>
<P>
A third thing is that leaders of financial organizations need
to be improved to avoid financial risks and corruption.
</P>
<P>
Wen also pointed to the need for a greater effort at
investigating major financial crimes to check the increase in
financial mishaps and financial organizations need to improve
services and do more for the country's economic development.
</P>
