<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1500 GMT, September 14 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA -- The United Nations Tuesday closed its besieged
compound in the East Timor capital of Dili after the evacuation of
1,300 East Timorese to Australia, a U.N. official said.
</P>
<P>
But the world body would leave about a dozen staff at a
different location in the city, Ian Martin, head of U.N.
Assistance Mission to East Timor (UNAMET), said in Darwin,
northern Australia. (UN-Dili-Closure)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CANBERRA -- Australian Prime Minister John Howard Tuesday
warned that the East Timor peacekeeping operation would be
dangerous and could result in casualties.
</P>
<P>
"There will be a danger. There could be casualties and the
Australian public should understand that," he told ABC television.
"It is a serious, dangerous operation."
</P>
<P>
"All I can say is they (the peacekeeping force) will be given
adequate legal authority to defend themselves and to take whatever
action is necessary to implement their mandate," he added. (
Australia-East Timor-Peacekeeping)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Pakistan Tuesday failed to hand over two Indian
soldiers captured last month as planned to the International
Committee of Red Cross (ICRC) due to a disagreement on the way of
transfer.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani Foreign Office spokesman Rafiq Altaf, addressing a
press briefing here, said Pakistan wanted to hand over the
captives under the glare of media to refrain India from any anti-
Pakistan propaganda.
</P>
<P>
"We want the journalists to witness that they are safe, sound,
in good health and good shape," he said. (Pakistan-India-Soldier)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WELLINGTON -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said here Tuesday
that it is of great importance to strengthen the relations between
China and New Zealand in the new international and regional
situation.
</P>
<P>
At a luncheon hosted in his honor by Governor-General of New
Zealand Michael Boys, Jiang Zemin said relations between China and
New Zealand have shown a good momentum of all-round development
with increasingly frequent exchanges of high-level visits, steady
growth of economic relations and trade and constantly broadened
scope of cooperation in recent years.
</P>
<P>
People-to-people contacts have become closer with the formal
launching of a tourist program that encourages Chinese citizens to
travel to New Zealand as tourists, Jiang said. (New Zealand-Jiang-
Visit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- British inflation rate fell to 1.1 percent in August,
the lowest since July 1963, the Office for National Statistics (
ONS) said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Underlying inflation, or RPIX, fell to 2.1 percent, the lowest
rate since October 1994, from 2.2 percent in July, said the ONS.
(UK-Inflation) 
</P>
