<HEADLINE> International Police in Pristina Increase to 500 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The international police
force in Pristina increased to 500 on September 13, a spokesman of
the United Nations mission in Kosovo announced in Pristina Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He said the chief task of the international police is to
protect all civilians in Pristina and restore law and order there.
</P>
<P>
They have been assigned jobs in various police stations in the
capital of Kosovo and international traffic police have been on
duty since September 13, the Tanjug said.
</P>
<P>
According to related U.N. resolutions, the U.N. mission in
Kosovo needs 31,000 international police.
</P>
<P>
On August 8, a 478-strong international police force from 10
countries began joining force with the peacekeepers in maintaining
public order in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
U.N. officials said that the public order in Kosovo has
deteriorated because of the delay in the arrival of international
police force due to the obstruction by some western countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
