<HEADLINE> Southern Chinese Economic Zone Planning High-Tech Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The city of Shenzhen, one of
China's special economic zones, in Guangdong Province, is
preparing for the First China International High-Tech Fair, from
October 5 to 10.
</P>
<P>
Some 31 Chinese provinces, autonomous regions, and
municipalities, and Hong Kong, Macao, and Taiwan have plans to
send delegations, an organizing committee official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Government delegations from Canada, Australia, Italy, Finland,
and more than a dozen other countries will attend, along with
representatives from 27 universities around the world.
</P>
<P>
The official reports that more than 120 Chinese students
studying overseas will return for the event, and 85 official
delegations and 2,856 companies and organizations will attend.
</P>
<P>
The fair will announce over 15,000 high-tech development
projects and research developments, according to the official. It
will be sponsored by the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation, Ministry of Science and Technology, Ministry of
Information Industry, Chinese Academy of Sciences, and Shenzhen
Government.
</P>
<P>
It will be China's third major international trade fair, after
the China Export Commodities Fair in Guangzhou and the China Fair
for International Investment and Trade in the city of Xiamen in
Fujian Province. 
