<HEADLINE> EU-Chinese Junior Managers Training Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- A group of junior managers
from companies in 15 European countries began to participate in
the EU-Chinese Junior Managers Training Program's second term,
which is launched here today.
</P>
<P>
The program is intended to help European companies learn more
about China's social and economic conditions to improve investment
in China.
</P>
<P>
At a reception today for students in the program, Ambassador
Endymion Wilkinson, the head of a delegation of the European
Commission, expressed his gratitude to all who have supported the
program.
</P>
<P>
In 12 to 15 months, students will attend symposia, meet with
Chinese senior officials, and visit successful companies.
</P>
<P>
The program was begun by the European Commission and China's
Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation. Its first term
started this March.  
</P>
