<HEADLINE> Heavy Fighting Storms Southern Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Fierce fighting once again
broke out Monday afternoon between the forces of Hussein Mohamed
Aidid and the combined militiamen of the Rahanwein Resistance Army
(RRA) and the Digil Salvation Army (DSA) for control of Qoryoley
town in southern Somalia.
</P>
<P>
According to eyewitnesses contacted before the telephone lines
of the town went off the air Monday afternoon, over one hundred
infantry militiamen of the RRA and DSA forces launched the attack
from the Sinkah area, just a few kilometers north of the town,
while eight battle wagons from Hussein Aidid's side were used in
counterattacking.
</P>
<P>
There are no official casualty figures available. However,
sources from the town said at least nine people were killed and
more than a dozen others were wounded. Though both sides have
claimed victory, witnesses said none of them got the upper hand
and the shooting subsided as darkness befell last night.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of families have fled the town to the neighboring
villages and towns. A businessman in Farhaneh village, about eight
kilometers East of Qoryoley town, said he believed that no single
civilian still remained in the town.
</P>
<P>
According to latest reports, the town of Qoryoley is calm
Tuesday, but the tension is still growing as the two sides
continue to strengthen their defensive positions outside the town
with Hussein Aidid's men still controlling the inner side of the
town.  
</P>
</TEXT>
