czttcocrcgvin
Commission (SEC) decided to reject the proposal of extending the
PSE trading hours, saying it will only call for more manipulations
in the equities market.
</P>
<P>
Liu discounted accusations that extension of the trading hours
will elicit more manipulations of stock prices while trading is
going on.
</P>
<P>
He said this will not happen because the PSE has its own rules
and regulations to follow in imposing sanctions against those
brokers who will engage in this illegal activity.
</P>
<P>
Right now, the Philippines is the only country in Asia that
limits its trading hours from 9:00 to 12:00 a.m. The neighboring
stock exchanges have made it a policy to trade well into the
afternoon hours, he explained.
</P>
<P>
He believed that approval by the SEC of the PSE board proposal
will mean more investments in the equities market.
</P>
<P>
He said that he already tried the same move when he was still
the PSE board chair but it was rejected by the SEC.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, he called on the PSE board to be persistent
in discussing the positive points that it could give to the
equities market once the proposal is considered by the SEC.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
