<HEADLINE> Irvine Signs for Jaguar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Ferrari driver Eddie Irvine,
currently joint-leader in the Formula One standings, Tuesday
confirmed that he had signed a three year contract to drive for
the newly formed Jaguar Racing starting next season.
</P>
<P>
According to reports from Coventry, the 33-year-old Ulsterman,
who grabbed a point in Sunday's Italian Grand Prix to join Finn
Mika Hakkinen on top of the world championship standings, had been
expected to join the team, which bought Stewart-Ford earlier in
the season.
</P>
<P>
Irvine said: "I'm overjoyed. I've been waiting for this
opportunity for the past two years."
</P>
<P>
"Through my experience in the re-building of Ferrari, I believe
I can make a significant contribution to Jaguar Racing," he added.
</P>
<P>
Dr Wolfgang Reitzle, Chairman of Jaguar, said that the signing
of Irvine, who will be partnered by veteran Englishman Johnny
Herbert, would enable the team to implement the changes needed for
next year's campaign.
</P>
<P>
Former Formula One legend Jackie Stewart, Chairman of Jaguar
Racing, specified why Irvine, who has won the Australian, Austrian
and German Grands Prix this year, had been their target.
</P>
<P>
Stewart said: "Its simple he has matured this year. He has come
of age." 
</P>
</TEXT>
