<HEADLINE> Largest Chinese Currency Loan For Overseas Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, September 14 (Xinhua)-- The Shenzhen branch of the
China Construction Bank (CCB), in Guangdong Province, today agreed
to provide 500 million yuan loans to the Bank of East Asia, whose
headquarters is in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
This is the largest loan in renminbi a Chinese bank has ever
made to an overseas bank and the first RMB overseas loan by a bank
in this special economic zone.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen recently got government permission for its branch
banks to deal in RMB, as part of the government's efforts to
encourage more cooperation with overseas banks.
</P>
<P>
Sun Jiancheng, the head of CCB's branch here, told Xinhua that
the bank is contacting other overseas banks in Shenzhen to help
them expand their RMB businesses.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen now has six overseas bank branches that can deal in
RMB. 
</P>
