<P>
HONG KONG, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Monetary
Authority (HKMA) said on Tuesday that there was a small increase
of 200 million HK dollars (25.64 million U.S. dollars) in foreign
assets of the Exchange Fund during August 1999.
</P>
<P>
HKMA released key data on the balance sheet of the Exchange
Fund at the end of August 1999, which are issued on a monthly
basis in accordance with the International Monetary Fund's Special
Data Dissemination Standard (SDDS) and are referred to as the
Analytical Accounts of the Central Bank under SDDS.
</P>
<P>
According to the data, foreign assets, representing the
external assets of the Exchange Fund, amounted to 655.1 billion HK
dollars (83.98 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The monetary base, comprising certificates of indebtedness and
coins issued, the aggregate balance of the banking system, and
exchange fund bills and notes issued, amounted to 196.6 billion HK
dollars (25.2 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Claims on the private sector in Hong Kong amounted to 54.6
billion HK dollars (7 billion U.S. dollars) at the end of August.
The increase of 6.2 billion HK dollars (794.8 million U.S. dollars)
from the previous month was mainly due to increases in both
foreign currency and Hong Kong dollar deposits placed with banks
in Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
