<DOCNO> XIE19990914.0185 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World's Biggest Hydro-Electric Power Project Moving Ahead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The Three Gorges Hydro-
electric Power project on China's Yangtze River, the biggest
project of its kind in the world, has been going smoothly in its
construction work and use of project funds.
</P>
<P>
A total of 42 billion yuan had been spent on the project by the
end of August and 8.4 million cubic meters of concrete had been
poured, according to one official.
</P>
<P>
More than 4,200 contracts were signed for the project, worth 32
billion yuan in total.
</P>
<P>
The project entered its second phase of construction with the
damming of the Yangtze in November of 1997. Cofferdams that were
completed during the second phase withstood the summer deluges on
the Yangtze in 1998 and 1999.
</P>
<P>
The second phase is scheduled for completion by 2003. By then,
18 million cubic meters of concrete will have been poured.
</P>
</TEXT>
