<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines Has More Than 5,000 Dengue Cases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- A total of 5,698 cases of
dengue fever has been reported in the Philippines as of September
10, 1999, the Health Department said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The report came from Dr. Lynetee Arce of the department's
National Epidemic Sentinel Surveillance System-Field Epidemiology
Training Program.
</P>
<P>
The dengue cases were reported from all regions of the country
since the start of the year, and most of them were from Central
Luzon Region with 1,819 cases, followed by the National Capital
Region with 1,249 cases.
</P>
<P>
The other areas with high number of cases was the southern
provinces of Nueva Ecija, Cebu, Tarlac and Misamis Oriental.
</P>
<P>
Arce also said in her report that 52 percent of the cases were
male and 48 percent were female, while 51 percent belonged to the
1-9 years age group.
</P>
<P>
Arce assured, however, that there was no clustering of cases
and no current "hot spots" or outbreaks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
