<DOCNO> XIE19990914.0218 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sees Steady Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- China's economy continued to
grow steadily in August pushed by increasing industrial production,
retail sales and exports, the National Bureau of Statistics said
today.
</P>
<P>
Fixed assets spending, which is considered to have a major
impetus to economic growth, totaled 990.8 billion yuan for the
January-August period, an increase of 10.4 percent from a year
earlier, the bureau said.
</P>
<P>
Total added value of output of the industrial sector for the
eight-month period was 1,267.9 billion yuan, up 9.4 percent on a
yearly basis; and the figure for August alone showed an increase
of 9.5 percent to 166.6 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
State industrial firms are becoming more efficient, said the
bureau, which based its observation on an 8.4-percent growth in
the added value produced by these firms in August.
</P>
<P>
Retail sales for last month amounted to 241.1 billion yuan,
growing by six percent from a year earlier, with the rate 0.4
percentage points higher than that in July. Total retail sales for
January-August reached 1,954.4 billion yuan, representing a year-
on-year increase of 6.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
In August the price level remained roughly the same as in July,
with the consumer price index down 1.3 percent and the retail
price index down 2.6 percent on a yearly basis.
</P>
<P>
According to Customs figures, China's exports in August
increased 17.8 percent year on year to 18.33 billion U.S. dollars,
with the growth rate 10.3 percentage points higher than in July,
while imports jumped 24 percent to 13.45 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
In the January-August period, China's total imports and exports
amounted to 220.8 billion U.S. dollars, up 7.3 percent year on
year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990914.0219 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
