<HEADLINE> WB to Provide Loan for India's AIDS Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank will provide
India a loan of 191 million U.S. dollars for the second national
AIDS control project.
</P>
<P>
The project is aimed at strengthening the country's capacity to
respond to the epidemic that is threatening to reverse
achievements in health and development.
</P>
<P>
An agreement for the International Development Association
(IDA) credit project approved in June, was signed here Tuesday by
Economic Affairs additional secretary V. Govindarajan and World
Bank country director Edwin Lim.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project is 229.80 million U.S. dollars.
The central and state governments will contribute 38.8 million
U.S. dollars and the remaining 191 million U.S. dollars would be
interest free IDA credit which works out to 140.82 million SDRs
(Special Drawing Rights). 
</P>
</TEXT>
