<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uganda to Issue Big Face Value Banknote </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
KAMPALA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of Uganda (BOU)
said on Tuesday that it would issue the banknote with a face value
of 20,000- shilling at the end of this year instead of in two
weeks' time as some media reported.
</P>
<P>
In a press release, BOU, the country's central bank, said that
it is true that some fake 20,000-shilling banknotes have been
circulating in the country, but the bank has no evidence that
rebels and armymen as well as businessmen are involved in the
production and circulation of counterfeited banknotes.
</P>
<P>
The BOU said it will continue to provide to the public advice
and information on such counterfeits and put new currency notes
into circulation through all commercial banks in the country.
</P>
<P>
It advised the general public to work closely with security
organs and report counterfeiting activities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
