<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Stagnates After Hitting Six-Week High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar
stagnated Tuesday, finishing little changed despite spiking to a
six-week high overnight on the back of a brighter commodity
picture.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar finished the local session at 65.49 U.S.
cents from Monday's close at 65.54, spending the local session
between 65.46 and 65.77.
</P>
<P>
Also at the local close, the Australian dollar was buying
0.6314 euro from 0.6327 at Monday's close and 69.54 Japanese yen
from 70.85.
</P>
<P>
In the money market, the 90-day bank bill rate was 5.01 percent
from 5.00 percent and the 180-day bill was 5.26 percent from 5.25
percent. 
</P>
