<HEADLINE> Silver Weak, Gold Steady in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Silver turned further weak
even as gold held steady Tuesday on the bullion market in Mumbai
(Bombay).
</P>
<P>
Ready silver (.999 fineness) dropped further sharply by 60
rupees (1.40 U.S. dollars) to close at 8,020 rupees (186.51 U.S.
dollars) per kilogram from the last weekend close of 8,080 rupees
(187.91 U.S. dollars) due to fall in the international prices and
good arrival.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, raw silver (.916 fineness) declined by 30 rupees
(0.70 U.S. dollars) to end at 7,915 rupees (184.07 U.S. dollars)
per kg from the previous close of 7,945 rupees (184.77 U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
Standard gold and 22-carat gold were steady at the previous
close of 4,080 rupees (94.88 U.S. dollars) and 3,775 rupees (87.79
U.S. dollars) per ten grams. 
</P>
