<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ningxia Reports Rise in Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Imports and exports for
northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region grew 11.7 percent
on a yearly basis to reach 189 million U.S. dollars in the first
seven months of this year.
</P>
<P>
This will provide a strong basis for the landlocked region to
achieve a nine-percent economic growth rate for 1999. Ningxia is
an economically less-advantaged region in the country.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities attribute the foreign trade increase in part
to the implementation of a series of preferential policies for
export-oriented enterprises with annual exports of more than eight
million yuan (about 960,000 dollars) each and foreign-funded
enterprises with annual exports of more than five million U.S.
dollars each.
</P>
<P>
The incentives, especially in terms of bank loans, have been
given to firms engaged in the production of 14 key export
commodities, including coal, magnesium and carborundum.
</P>
<P>
While consolidating traditional markets such as the United
States and Japan, Ningxia is making efforts to expand into other
overseas markets.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990914.0226 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S.Asian Human Development Report Issued in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 14 (Xinhua) -- A Pakistani think tank
Tuesday launched the Report on Human Development in South Asia
1999 here, focusing on the reasons behind the human deprivation in
the region.
</P>
<P>
"The unique feature of this report is the concept of humane
governance that puts people at the center of all governance
policies, strategies, and actions," said Khadija Haq, president of
the Islamabad-based Mahbub ul Haq Human Development Center (HDC).
</P>
<P>
The center held the inaugural launch of the report in
collaboration with the United Nations Development Program (UNDP).
</P>
<P>
The 1999 report, the third in a series on the challenges to
human development in South Asia, presents a multi-faceted picture
of the region's crisis of governance and suggests governance
reforms and implementation strategies to advance human
development.
</P>
<P>
South Asia, with nearly one-fourth of humanity, has emerged as
the most illiterate, the poorest, the most malnourished, and the
least gender-sensitive region in the world, according to the first
two reports on human development in South Asia in 1997 and 1998.
</P>
<P>
The 1999 report says that South Asia has emerged as one of the
most poorly-governed regions in the world. Consequently it focuses
on what South Asia's governments and civil societies can do to
reverse these trends and bring the region back on the path of
humane and responsible development.
</P>
<P>
The HDC was set up in November 1995 in Islamabad, Pakistan, as
a policy research institute and think tank by late Dr. Mahbub ul
Haq, founder and chief architect of UNDP's Human Development
Reports.
</P>
<P>
It is committed to organizing professional research, policy
studies and seminars in the area of human development, with a
special focus on the South Asia region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
