<HEADLINE> Over 25 Nations to Take Part in World Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
in Uganda
</P>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- More than 25 countries are
to take part in the seventh annual Uganda International Trade
Fair (UITF) early next month, a press release from the Uganda
Manufacturers' Association (UMA) said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
President Yoweri Museveni is expected to open the week-long
trade fair on October 7, it added.
</P>
<P>
So far over 400 exhibitors have applied to take part in the
trade fair and UITF has registered a steady growth since its
inception in 1993, when 220 exhibitors from eight countries
participated.
</P>
<P>
UMA Executive Director Hillary Obonyo told a press conference
Monday that the first phase of the trade fair is specifically
reserved for business, and the second part will be for school
children. 
