<HEADLINE> Nets Center Williams to Undergo Knee Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Center Jayson Williams
still needs more work done on his battered body as New Jersey Nets
announced he will undergo arthroscopic surgery on the right knee
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The operation is expected to clean out loose particles in the
knee after doctors inserted a plate and five screws in his bone on
April 2.
</P>
<P>
Williams had broken his right leg the day before when he
collided with teammate Stephon Marbury and underwent an extensive
surgery.
