<HEADLINE> Afghan Opposition Announces Interim Leadership Body </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The Afghan opposition
United Front Tuesday declared the setup of an interim emergency
Political Office headed by deposed president Burhanuddin Rabbani
and announced names for a 10-member new cabinet.
</P>
<P>
The Political Office of the Leadership Council will oversee the
implementation of broad political as well as military policies of
the United Front, spokesman for the anti-Taliban alliance General
Hussain Anwari said in a statement reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The Political Office will temporarily assume the role of the
Leadership Council until the full membership of the Leadership
Council meets next in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Members of the Political Office are: Prof. Burhanuddin Rabbani
(chairman), Ustad Abdul Rab Rassoul Sayaf (deputy chairman), Abdul
Raheem Abbas Karimi (secretary), Ahmad Shah Masood, Sayed Hussain
Anwari, Hajy Abdul Qadir, Qurban Ali Erfani, Wahidullah Sabaoon,
Sayed Noorullah Emad and Abdullah Wardak.
</P>
<P>
The 10-member cabinet announced include Sarapoh Mohammad Qassim
(justice minister), engineer Gardezee (agricultural minister, only
one name), Mohammad Elyass Zaraa (education minister), Mohammad
Hashim Sa'ee (public works minister), Mohammad Nateqi (commerce
minister), Wahidullah Sabaoon (finance minister), Dr. Abdullah
(deputy and acting foreign minister, only one name), Dr. Yaqub
Barekzai (health minister), Faheem Khan (minister of state for
security matters) and Qazi Abdul Bari (deputy justice of the high
and supreme courts). 
</P>
