<HEADLINE> DPR Korea, South Korea Plan Friendly Basketball Matches </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic People's
Republic of Korea and South Korea will begin their second sports
exchange with a series of friendly basketball games later this
month, organizers said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Men's and women's basketball teams of South Korea's Hyundai
Group will play four matches with their northern counterparts
September 28-29 in Pyongyang.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made by Kim Ko-joong, a Hyundai executive
who just returned from a visit to DPR Korea, where he held
discussions with DPR Korean officials.
</P>
<P>
It marks the second sports exchange between the two sides in
less than two months, following two friendly soccer games in
Pyongyang in early August between workers from both sides.
