<HEADLINE> Cambodia's Population Reaches 11.4 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia Tuesday released
the final results of the 1998 census which put the country's
population at 11.4 million, double the figure recorded by the last
census 36 years earlier.
</P>
<P>
The last census conducted in 1962 put Cambodia's population
then at 5.7 million. The present census was conducted in March
1998.
</P>
<P>
About 25,000 enumerators and 8,350 supervisors, apart from
thousands of supervisory and supporting staff at the province,
district and commune levels, collected information by house to
house visits during the census.
</P>
<P>
The population of 11,437,656 occupies the seventh position
among the first 10 most populous countries in Southeast Asia.
Cambodia's average annual population growth rate of 2.49 percent
is relatively higher than neighboring Vietnam's 1.8 percent and
Thailand's 1.0 percent and marginally lower than Laos' 3.0
percent.
</P>
<P>
Among the 24 provinces and municipalities, Kompong Cham is the
biggest province which has about 14 percent of the country's
population, while Pailin municipality is the smallest unit in
terms of population.
</P>
<P>
According to the census, about 84 percent of the population
live in rural areas, with urban population accounting for only
15.7 percent. The average size of normal or regular households is
5.2 persons at the national level.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia has a young population with 42.8 percent in the age
group from 0 to 14. On the whole, nearly 83 percent of the
literate population aged 25 and over have not gone beyond the
primary level of education. And only about 64 percent of the
children aged between 7 and 14 attend schools. And in the urban
areas more than three-quarters of the children are attending
schools.
</P>
<P>
"There is a deficit of adult males resulting primarily from
civil war and large scale mortality during the seventies," said
Sar Kheng, deputy prime minister and co-minister of interior on
the occasion of the release of the census results.
</P>
<P>
The census also revealed that the sex ratio of the population
(number of males per hundred females) is 93.0, but for the
population aged 15 years and over is 85.2 and for the group aged
60 years and over is only 71.8.
</P>
<P>
Cambodia's territory is 181,035 square kilometers with a
density of population of 64 persons per square kilometer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
