<HEADLINE> China Satisfied with Auckland Summit Results: FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Auckland summit is another important meeting between the
two leaders after they had accomplished bilateral visits with
successes, and will help push the recovery, improvement and
development of Sino-U.S. relations, Sun said at a routine press
conference here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that during the meeting, the two sides
expressed their will to devote efforts to building a constructive
strategic partnership oriented toward the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang elaborated on China's principles and stance on
the Taiwan issue, and President Clinton reiterated that the U.S.
government will continue to honor its "one China" policy,
according to Sun.
</P>
<P>
Both Jiang and Clinton believed that the summit will have a
positive effect on the Sino-U.S. talks on China's entry into the
World Trade Organization, Sun said.  
</P>
