<DOCNO> XIE19990914.0252 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Top Legislator Meets Albanian Guests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, met here
today with an Albanian People's Assembly (APA) delegation led by
Sabri Godo, chairman of the assembly's Commission of Foreign
Affairs.
</P>
<P>
Li said China and Albania enjoy traditional friendship and
growth of bilateral ties was "generally smooth".
</P>
<P>
China respects the development path chosen by Albania, he said,
adding that the increased contacts between the NPC and APA
deepened bilateral ties. He hoped the guests could better
understand China, which would promote better understanding between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Li also briefed the guests on China's reform and opening-up
cause. "Our experience demonstrates that the development of a
country should be based on a development pattern suitable to its
national conditions," he said.
</P>
<P>
On the Taiwan issue, Li expressed his appreciation to the "one
China" policy adopted by the Albanian government and its People's
Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Regarding the international situation, he said that China
adopts an independent foreign policy of peace. "In our view, the
world should be a multi-polar globe because a multi-polar world is
safer than the single-polar world," he said. Also, he wished peace
and stability to the Balkans and other regions of the world.
</P>
<P>
Godo expressed his admiration for China's rapid development
since the reform and opening-up and his congratulations on the
50th anniversary of the founding of the People's Republic of China.
Even with some turns and twists, the two countries can open a new
chapter in their bilateral ties, he said.
</P>
<P>
In another development on Monday, Zeng Jianhui, chairman of the
NPC Foreign Affairs Committee, hosted working talks with the
delegation, during which the two sides exchanges views on
enhancement of inter-parliament exchanges and friendly cooperation.
Godo reiterated on that occasion that the Albania government and
its People's Assembly recognize only one China -- the People's
Republic of China. Such a stance will not have any change, he
stressed.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian guests arrived here on Sunday for a goodwill visit
at the invitation of the NPC Foreign Affairs Committee.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
