takes some skill to get it to the right place," he added.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia Monday night gave in-principle permission for the
drops to go ahead in the mountains of East Timor where tens of
thousands of displaced people have taken refuge, some reportedly
surviving on roots and leaves.
</P>
<P>
AusAID is stockpiling tons of food and medical supplies in a
1,500 square-meter warehouse leased near the airport of Darwin in
northern Australia.
</P>
<P>
The first drops will comprise rice, cooking utensils, medical
kits, materials for constructing shelters and water containers,
the spokesman said. 
