government-owned Metropolitan Waterfronts and Sewerage System
which provides water and sewerage services to Metro Manila, Rizal
province and part of Cavite province.
</P>
<P>
The ADB assistance is part of a 350-million-dollar debt package
being raised by the water firm to meet its financing needs up to
the year 2002. Beyond that time, revenues are expected to reach
self-sustaining levels.
</P>
<P>
Other financiers include the European Bank and a syndicate of
international commercial banks. 
