<HEADLINE> UPU Director Impressed by Hangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU,September 14 (Xinhua) -- Thomas Leavey,general
director of the International Bureau of the Universal Postal Union
(UPU), said during a visit to Hangzhou Monday that he was
impressed by its beautiful scenery.
</P>
<P>
Leavey came here along with more than 1,000 delegates attending
the ongoing 22nd Universal Postal Congress (UPC) in Beijing,
</P>
<P>
They visited West Lake, an attraction in western Hangzhou
renowned for its scenic splendor, and arts and crafts shops
specializing in delicate wood carvings, embroidery, paper-cuttings
and silk umbrellas.
</P>
<P>
Andre Darrigrand, the senior member of UPC, said he was
delighted to visit Hangzhou and hoped to come to the city in east
China's Zhejiang Province again someday.
</P>
<P>
The delegates arrived from Shanghai, China's leading industrial
and commercial city, where they visited the Oriental Pearl TV
Tower, the Jinqiao Export Processing and Trade Zone, the Shanghai
Museum, and Yuyuan Park. 
</P>
