<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexico Becomes Largest Car Producer in L. America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Mexico has surpassed
Brazil for the first time as the largest car producer in Latin
America, the local press reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
According to the local weekly Latin American Mercantile Gazette,
Mexico's car production hit 856,700 units during the first six
months of the year, compared with 757,700 units produced by Brazil
during the same period.
</P>
<P>
Mexico's annual car production is expected to reach 1.6 million
units this year, exceeding Brazil's 1.4 million. United States is
the biggest automobile market for Mexico.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1.34 million units made last year in Mexico, 984,000 or
73.5 percent were for the U.S. market.
</P>
<P>
The North American Free Trade Agreement (NAFTA) has served as
an accelerator for the shipment of Mexican-made cars to the United
States, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The largest U.S. car manufacturers such as Chrysler, Ford and
General Motors have numerous assembly plants in Mexico. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
