<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nordic Nations Carry out One-Week Military Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The Nordic nations started a
one-week joint military maneuver Monday, dubbed "Nordic Peace 99,"
in Satakunta, southwest of Finland.
</P>
<P>
National Defense Troops from Sweden, Norway, Denmark and
Finland participated in the exercise, which is aimed at
coordinating international peace-keeping actions and enhancing
their capabilities for handling crises.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 2,000 soldiers and civil servicemen, together with more
than 100 vessels and helicopters, took part in the drill, which
hypothetically involved two neighboring countries fighting a war.
</P>
<P>
The Finnish President Martti Ahtisaari and the defense
ministers of the four Nordic nations attended the military
exercise. Observers from Russia and Baltic Sea countries were also
invited.
</P>
<P>
This is the third joint military exercise carried out among
Nordic nations, the two former ones were held in Sweden and Norway.
</P>
</TEXT>
