<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Watford Signs Wooter from Real Zaragoza </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Watford smashed their transfer
record by signing Nordin Wooter from Real Zaragoza for 950,000
pounds on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old Dutch striker, who came through the much-touted
Ajax youth system, has been capped by the Netherlands at both
under-18 and under-21 level.
</P>
<P>
Wooter's arrival at Vicarage Road almost doubles the previous
club record of 550,000 pounds paid to AC Milan in 1984 to bring
back Luther Blissett.
</P>
<P>
The Hornets will not be able to field him in the Worthington
Cup against Wigan but manager Graham Taylor hopes to receive
international clearance in time to include him for the visit of
Chelsea on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time Taylor has paid money for a player since
Watford were promoted to the Premiership - the previous three
signings this summer were free transfers.
</P>
<P>
"I see Nordin as a decided asset - he is a creative, attacking
player and I'm sure most supporters will agree that is something
we have been short of since the start of this season," said Taylor.
</P>
<P>
"He can play as a winger or striker and I look forward to
working with him, and hopefully earn him a place in the full Dutch
national team."
</P>
<P>
Wooter, who was on trial with Derby this summer, said: "I am
very pleased to have signed for Watford.
</P>
<P>
"Graham Taylor has been very good to me and the players here
have made me feel really welcome and part of the squad," he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
