<HEADLINE> IAAF Ratifies World Mark by American Pole Vaulter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The International Amateur
Athletic Federation Monday officially recognized American pole
vaulter Stacy Dragila as the world record holder.
</P>
<P>
Dragila registered a winning performance of 4.60 meters at last
month's world championships in Seville, Spain, equaling the mark
set by Australia's Emma George on February 20.
</P>
<P>
Still to be officially ratified from Seville is Michael Johnson
's world record of 43.18 seconds in the 400 meters. That time
shattered Butch Reynolds' 11-year-old mark of 43.29. 
</P>
</TEXT>
