<HEADLINE> Voeller Named Ambassador for German World Cup Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Former German striker Rudi
Voeller was Appointed Monday as ambassador to boost his country's
2006 World Cup bid.
</P>
<P>
Voeller, who was capped 90 times for Germany, became the fourth
former German international to assist in the job after the German
Football Federation chose Juergen Klinsmann, Guenter Netzer and
Karl-Heinz Rummenigge for the bid.
</P>
<P>
The executive committee of football's world governing body FIFA
will decide next July who will stage the event. Also in the race
are Brazil, England, Morocco and South Africa. 
</P>
