<HEADLINE> Fair Aimed to Strengthen Steel Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The '99 China Steel Products
Fair will be held from October 8-10 in Guangzhou, capital of south
China's Guangdong Province, today's China Daily says.
</P>
<P>
Huang Shuhe, deputy secretary-general of the State Economic and
Trade Commission (SETC), said that the aim of hosting such an
activity is to promote the healthy development of the steel
industry in the market-orientated economy.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the SETC, the State Internal Trade Bureau (SITB)
and the State Metallurgical Industry Bureau (SMIB), the event is
the first steel product fair held by three government departments.
</P>
<P>
"The fair is aimed to improve the relationship between the
producer, supplier and buyer, and facilitate the industry to solve
the current structural problems," said Ding Junfa, deputy director
of SITB.
</P>
<P>
Several trade fairs covering the production and circulation of
steel products will also be launched during the event.
</P>
<P>
China's steel output totaled 110 million tons last year,
ranking first in the world for three consecutive years. 
