<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil's Oil Imports Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's oil imports
decreased 12.9 percent in the first eight months of this year,
according to data released Monday by Brazil's state oil company,
Petrobras.
</P>
<P>
By the end of August, Brazil had imported oil worth 1.28
billion dollars, compared with 1.47 billion dollars of oil
imported during the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Brazil's imported oil amounted to 405,000 barrels per day (bpd)
of oil this year, against 497,000 bpd last year.
</P>
<P>
Brazil, which has the largest economy in Latin America, can
only provide 65 percent of its domestic need for petroleum with
its own production.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
